- QuickJS / MicroQuickJS is an open source JavaScript engine, and there is confirmed high-severity risk exposure tied to CVE-2025-62495.  
- The patch target you should plan around is the 2025-09-13 fix window, and the project is associated with Fabrice Bellard.  
- Treat this as a real exposure if you ship or embed QuickJS anywhere in your stack; prioritize identifying every binary, repo, container, and vendored copy.  
- I’d recommend a 3-step patch plan: inventory, upgrade/replace, then verify with rebuilds and regression tests.

