Salesforce Agentforce likely means the market is moving from “buy software” to “buy outcomes delivered by agents.”

For positioning, I’d think about it this way:
- Salesforce is trying to own the AI agent layer inside the CRM stack, not just a feature set.  
- That pushes the conversation from workflow automation to autonomous task completion.  
- If you sell into Salesforce customers, your message should avoid “we also have AI agents” and instead sharpen on where you’re better:
  - deeper domain expertise
  - faster time to value
  - cross-system orchestration
  - stronger governance / observability
